<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Russulaceae" genus="Lactarius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Lactarius repraesentaneus" order="Russulales" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="repraesentaneus">
<pageBreakToken pageId="13" pageNumber="14" start="start">Lactarius</pageBreakToken>
repraesentaneus
</taxonomicName>
The following morphological description includes data from Colorado specimens listed in 
<bibRefCitation author="Barge, EG" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="414 - 440" title="Systematics of the ectomycorrhizal genus Lactarius in the Rocky Mountains alpine zone." url="10.3852/15-177" volume="108" year="2016">Barge et al. (2016)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
